The Helios Airways flight ZU522 crashed near Athens, sparking anger among relatives demanding answers.
Reports of past decompression issues fueled suspicions of technical faults.
Experts suggested the crew could have tried to lower the altitude if there was a loss of cabin pressure.
Eyewitnesses described the horrific scene of the crash, with scattered bodies and debris.
The Greek government confirmed no signs of terrorism, emphasizing a possible mechanical failure.
Condolences poured in for the 121 victims, including 48 children, as investigations into the tragic event continued.
